Lab Name: Authentication bypass via flawed state machine
Category: Business Logic Vulnerabilities
Difficulty: Expert
Objective: Exploit incorrect application state transitions to access authenticated functionality without completing the normal login process.

Vulnerability Description

The application assumes users move through authentication steps in a fixed order. By manipulating requests or navigating directly to specific endpoints, an attacker can place the application into an unexpected state where authentication checks are skipped.

This is a business logic flaw caused by improper enforcement of application state.

Exploitation Steps

1. Observe the normal authentication workflow using Burp Suite.


2. Identify the requests responsible for changing the user's role and drop the get request by stopping all the requests after logging in 


3. Only POST request will be sent and GET will br dropped leading to loss of any role assigning hence application assigns admin role by default giving admin privileges.

4. Leading to access of protected functionality without successfully completing authentication.


5. Verify unauthorized access and solve the lab.

Impact

Authentication bypass.

Unauthorized access to protected resources.

Privilege escalation.

Compromise of application security.

Root Cause

The application relies on assumptions about the order of operations instead of verifying authentication status on every protected request.

Remediation

Validate authentication and authorization on every request.

Enforce strict server-side state transitions.

Prevent users from skipping required workflow steps.

Reject requests that do not follow the expected authentication sequence.